text.tspan: Diarrheal disease death rates vs. GDP per capita, 2016
Diarrheal disease death rates, measured per 100,000 individuals versus gross domestic product (GDP) per capita,
measured in 2011 international-$. Death rates are given as age-standardized rates which assumes a constant age
distribution across the population to allow for comparison across countries and through time.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (GBD), World Bank – WDI
